  <!-- Overview -->
  <section class="ed-section">
    <div class="ed-section-head"><h2>The trip</h2></div>
    <div class="ed-prose">
      <p>A lakefront house on Lake Hartwell, about 1 hour 15 minutes from Greenville via I-85. The private dock is covered, has deep water for swimming, and fish bite right off it. A pontoon rental for the middle of the week rounds it out.</p>
    </div>
    <dl class="ed-kv" style="margin-top:18px;">
      <dt>Check-in</dt><dd>4:00 PM</dd>
      <dt>Checkout</dt><dd>11:00 AM</dd>
      <dt>Address</dt><dd><a class="ed-link" href="https://www.google.com/maps/search/675+Old+Mill+Road+Hartwell+GA+30643" target="_blank">675 Old Mill Road, Hartwell, GA 30643</a></dd>
      <dt>Listing</dt><dd><a class="ed-link" href="https://www.airbnb.com/rooms/934751170644664612" target="_blank">View on Airbnb</a></dd>
    </dl>
  </section>

  <!-- The house -->
  <section class="ed-section">
    <div class="ed-section-head"><h2>The house</h2></div>
    <div class="ed-prose">
      <p>An Airbnb Guest Favorite. Reviewers call out the well-stocked kitchen and comfortable beds. A paved walkway runs from the house down to the covered dock, so all ages can get to the water easily.</p>
    </div>
    <dl class="ed-kv" style="margin-top:18px;">
      <dt>Sleeping</dt><dd>6 king bedrooms (4 en suite on the main level) plus a kids' room with 2 bunk beds and a toddler bed. 10 beds across 7 bedrooms.</dd>
      <dt>Bathrooms</dt><dd>5.5</dd>
      <dt>Dock</dt><dd>Covered, deep-water, private boat slip. Swimmable, and you can fish right off it.</dd>
    </dl>
    <div class="ed-tags" style="margin-top:18px;">
      <span class="ed-tag">Full kitchen</span>
      <span class="ed-tag">BBQ grill</span>
      <span class="ed-tag">Fire pit</span>
      <span class="ed-tag">Pool table</span>
      <span class="ed-tag">Ping pong</span>
      <span class="ed-tag">Kayak</span>
      <span class="ed-tag">Board games</span>
      <span class="ed-tag">Kids' dinnerware</span>
      <span class="ed-tag">Outdoor dining</span>
      <span class="ed-tag">Pet friendly</span>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Pontoon -->
  <section class="ed-section">
    <div class="ed-section-head"><h2>The boat</h2><div class="aside">Booked</div></div>
    <div class="ed-prose">
      <p>A pontoon is booked for four days through <a class="ed-link" href="https://www.boatsetter.com" target="_blank">Boatsetter</a>, picked up on the Anderson, SC side of the lake. Self-drive, no captain.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="ed-grid" style="margin-top:18px;">

      <div class="ed-cell">
        <div class="ttl">The boat</div>
        <div class="body">
          <strong>2014 Premier 220 SunSation RE</strong>
          <div class="leg">
            Tritoon (triple tube), 150hp, 22 ft. Seats up to 12. Bluetooth stereo, swim ladder, anchor, and life jackets aboard. Pulls tubes easily; wakeboarding is doable but not aggressive.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="ed-cell">
        <div class="ttl">Schedule</div>
        <div class="body">
          <strong>Tue Jul 7 – Fri Jul 10</strong>
          <div class="leg">
            Pickup Tue Jul 7 at 8:30 AM. Return Fri Jul 10 by 6:00 PM. Four full days on the water.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="ed-cell">
        <div class="ttl">Pickup</div>
        <div class="body">
          <strong><a class="ed-link" href="https://www.google.com/maps/search/117+Chestnut+Lane+Anderson+SC+29625" target="_blank">117 Chestnut Lane, Anderson, SC</a></strong>
          <div class="leg">
            About 35 minutes from the house, on the Anderson side of the lake. Pickup at 8:30 AM.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="ed-cell">
        <div class="ttl">Good to know</div>
        <div class="body">
          <div class="leg">
            Fuel isn't included, so top it off before returning to avoid a fee. Don't be late bringing it back.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

